<p>Huzzah!</p>

<p>A new order has been placed for: </p>

<ul>
  <% @order.sold_items.each do |si| %>
    <li><%= "#{si.quantity} * #{si.product.name}, #{number_to_currency((si.total_paid.to_f / 100), unit: '£')}" %></li>
  <% end %>
  <li>And of course, the ubiquitous delivery cost of <%= number_to_currency((@order.paid_shipping_price.to_f / 100), unit: '£').html_safe %></li>
  <li>Totalling <%= number_to_currency((@order.total_paid_amount.to_f / 100), unit: '£').html_safe %></li>
</ul>

<p>That's our <%= @orders_in_last_30_days.count.ordinalize %> in the last 30 days, giving a revenue of to <%= number_to_currency((@orders_in_last_30_days.map{|o| o.total_paid_amount}.sum.to_f / 100), unit: '£').html_safe %></p>

<p>Keep pushing.</p>

